        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>If the scrofin is wrestling a foe as part of a challenge and takes damage, or when it is reduced to half its hp maximum, it becomes angry. While angry, the scrofin has advantage on melee attack rolls and on saving throws against spells or effects that would &amp;Reference[condition=charmed]{charm} or &amp;Reference[condition=frightened]{frighten} it or make it &amp;Reference[condition=unconscious], and it has resistance to bludgeoning damage. It remains angry for 1 minute, or until it is knocked &amp;Reference[condition=unconscious]. Alternatively, it can end its anger as a bonus action.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>",
